dashboard.definition:
{
  "title": "Icon Library \u2014 README",
  "description": "Complete guide to configuring the Icon Library visualization, with live demos for drilldown, threshold colors, and threshold effects, plus the bundled SVG catalog and CSV lookup.",
  "dataSources": {
    "ds_stub": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "stub"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "1"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Stub for static icon rendering"
    },
    "ds_data_driven": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "icon"
            },
            {
              "name": "color"
            },
            {
              "name": "label"
            },
            {
              "name": "value"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "security"
            ],
            [
              "#22C55E"
            ],
            [
              "Secure"
            ],
            [
              "95"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Data-driven demo (SPL columns drive icon, color, label)"
    },
    "ds_thr_low": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "value"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "20"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Threshold demo \u2014 value=20 (low band)"
    },
    "ds_thr_mid": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "value"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "65"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Threshold demo \u2014 value=65 (mid band)"
    },
    "ds_thr_high": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "value"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "97"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Threshold demo \u2014 value=97 (high band)"
    },
    "ds_fx_critical": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "value"
            },
            {
              "name": "label"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "25"
            ],
            [
              "value=25"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Effects demo \u2014 critical band"
    },
    "ds_fx_warning": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "value"
            },
            {
              "name": "label"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "70"
            ],
            [
              "value=70"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Effects demo \u2014 warning band"
    },
    "ds_fx_healthy": {
      "type": "ds.test",
      "options": {
        "data": {
          "fields": [
            {
              "name": "value"
            },
            {
              "name": "label"
            }
          ],
          "columns": [
            [
              "95"
            ],
            [
              "value=95"
            ]
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Effects demo \u2014 healthy band"
    },
    "ds_drilldown_icons": {
      "type": "ds.search",
      "options": {
        "query": "| makeresults | eval icon=\"security\", label=\"Click me\""
      },
      "name": "Drilldown demo source (real ds.search \u2014 required for setToken)"
    }
  },
  "defaults": {
    "tokens": {
      "default": {
        "selected_icon": {
          "value": "(click the icon below)"
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "inputs": {},
  "visualizations": {
    "viz_title": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "# Icon Library for Splunk Dashboard Studio\n\nA Splunk Cloud\u2013ready icon toolkit with **three** ways to use it: a custom **visualization** for rendering any of 3,879 Material Symbols icons with threshold-driven coloring and click drilldown; a bundled **SVG asset catalog** drop-in for `splunk.image` elements; and a **CSV lookup** (`| inputlookup icon_catalog`) for enumerating icons from SPL.\n\n**Font:** [Material Symbols Outlined](https://fonts.google.com/icons) \u2014 base64-embedded in `visualization.css`, no external requests. **SVG catalog:** 3,879 files under `appserver/static/icons/<category>/<name>.svg`.",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_demo_basic": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_stub"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconName": "rocket_launch",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconColor": "#06B6D4"
      }
    },
    "viz_demo_labeled": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_stub"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconName": "security",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconColor": "#22C55E",
        "icon_library.icon_library.showLabel": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.labelText": "Secure",
        "icon_library.icon_library.labelColor": "#94A3B8",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgShape": "circle",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgColor": "#0F172A",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgPadding": "20"
      }
    },
    "viz_demo_glow": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_stub"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconName": "electric_bolt",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconColor": "#F59E0B",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glow": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowColor": "#F59E0B",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowSize": "18"
      }
    },
    "viz_demo_combo": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_stub"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconName": "shield",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconColor": "#8B5CF6",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glow": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowColor": "#8B5CF6",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowSize": "12",
        "icon_library.icon_library.shadow": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.shadowBlur": "10",
        "icon_library.icon_library.shadowOffsetY": "4",
        "icon_library.icon_library.showLabel": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.labelText": "Protected",
        "icon_library.icon_library.labelColor": "#CBD5E1",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgShape": "rounded_rect",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgColor": "#1A1A2E",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgPadding": "16",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgRadius": "14"
      }
    },
    "viz_demo_data": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_data_driven"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconColor": "#06B6D4",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glow": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowColor": "#22C55E",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowSize": "10"
      }
    },
    "viz_sec1": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 1. Quick Start\n\n1. Open Dashboard Studio and create or edit a dashboard.\n2. Add a panel and set its visualization type to **Icon Library** (`icon_library.icon_library`).\n3. In the panel `options`, add `\"backgroundColor\": \"transparent\"` \u2014 Dashboard Studio defaults custom-viz panels to a dark fill that hides the icon behind a black box.\n4. Pick an icon from the **Icon (Popular)** dropdown \u2014 or type any Material Symbols name (e.g. `mode_heat_off`) in the **Custom Icon Name** field. For browsing all 3,879 icons visually, use the bundled **Icon Catalog (SVG Browser)** dashboard.\n5. Adjust color, background, glow, label, threshold colors, threshold effects, tooltip, and theme in the formatter sidebar.\n\nThe visualization works **with or without** an attached search. Without one, it renders purely from formatter config.\n\n### Minimal panel JSON\n\n```json\n\"viz_status\": {\n  \"type\": \"icon_library.icon_library\",\n  \"options\": {\n    \"backgroundColor\": \"transparent\",\n    \"icon_library.icon_library.iconName\": \"rocket_launch\",\n    \"icon_library.icon_library.iconColor\": \"#06B6D4\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n> The four demo tiles in the top right of this dashboard render with the configurations shown in `viz_demo_basic`, `viz_demo_labeled`, `viz_demo_glow`, and `viz_demo_combo`.",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_sec2": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 2. Finding Icon Names\n\nThere are three ways to browse the catalog:\n\n- **Visual browser inside Splunk:** Open the **Icon Catalog (SVG Browser)** dashboard bundled with this app \u2014 filter by name or tag, narrow by category, see preview tiles update live.\n- **SPL:** `| inputlookup icon_catalog` returns all 3,879 icons with their category, path, tags, and Google popularity score. Filter with `search tags=*shield*` or `where category=\"alert\"`.\n- **External:** [fonts.google.com/icons](https://fonts.google.com/icons) \u2014 the canonical Google reference.\n\n### Syntax rules\n\n- Use **lowercase_with_underscores** only.\n- Examples: `home`, `rocket_launch`, `mode_heat_off`, `nest_thermostat`, `monitor_heart`.\n- Invalid characters are stripped automatically by the viz (e.g. `Mode Heat Off` \u2192 `modeheatoff`).\n- Set via the **Custom Icon Name** formatter field (overrides the dropdown), or the SPL `icon` column (overrides both).\n\n### Three ways to set the icon, in priority order\n\n**1. SPL `icon` column** (highest priority \u2014 data-driven):\n\n```spl\n| makeresults | eval icon=\"security\"\n```\n\n**2. `customIcon` formatter option** (JSON or sidebar field):\n\n```json\n\"options\": {\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.customIcon\": \"mode_heat_off\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.iconColor\": \"#EF4444\"\n}\n```\n\n**3. `iconName` formatter dropdown** (fallback, only ~150 popular icons):\n\n```json\n\"options\": { \"icon_library.icon_library.iconName\": \"home\" }\n```\n\n### Threshold effects can also override the icon\n\nWhen the Threshold colors engine is active and the `thresholdIconLow/Mid/High` formatter fields are non-empty, the icon swaps based on the value band (see Section 7).",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_sec3": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 3. SVG Catalog & CSV Lookup\n\nBeyond the custom viz, this app bundles **3,879 Material Symbols Outlined SVGs** and a searchable lookup. Use them when you don't need a full custom viz panel \u2014 for example, in `splunk.image` elements, asset slots, HTML markdown, or CSS backgrounds. These render in the parent document with no iframe overhead, so they scale to high-density dashboards better than the custom viz.\n\n### Where the SVGs live\n\n```\n$SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/icon_library/appserver/static/icons/<category>/<name>.svg\n```\n\nServed by Splunk at:\n\n```\n/static/app/icon_library/icons/<category>/<name>.svg\n```\n\n19 folders: 18 official Google categories (`action`, `image`, `maps`, `social`, `av`, `editor`, `device`, `communication`, `places`, `content`, `hardware`, `notification`, `navigation`, `file`, `search`, `home`, `toggle`, `alert`) + `_other` for icons not yet classified by Google.\n\n### Drop into a Studio splunk.image element\n\n```json\n\"viz_my_icon\": {\n  \"type\": \"splunk.image\",\n  \"options\": {\n    \"src\": \"/static/app/icon_library/icons/action/check_circle.svg\",\n    \"backgroundColor\": \"#F8FAFC\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n(SVGs ship with black `fill` \u2014 wrap on a light card or set the element's `backgroundColor` to make them visible on dark dashboards.)\n\n### Query the catalog from SPL\n\n```spl\n| inputlookup icon_catalog\n| search tags=*shield* OR name=*shield*\n| sort -popularity\n| table name, category, path, tags\n```\n\nColumns: `name`, `category`, `path` (full URL), `tags` (pipe-separated Google search keywords), `popularity` (Google's usage score \u2014 higher is more common).\n\n### When to use which\n\n| Need | Use |\n|---|---|\n| Threshold coloring, pulse animation, drilldown, glow, multi-band effects | **Custom viz** (Sections 4\u20137) |\n| Many tiles (50+) where iframe overhead matters | **SVG catalog** with `splunk.image` |\n| Programmatic icon picking from a search | **CSV lookup** in SPL \u2192 feed into the custom viz or splunk.image |",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_sec4": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 4. Configuration Reference\n\nAll options are namespaced **`icon_library.icon_library.<key>`** in Dashboard Studio JSON. The formatter sidebar accepts the bare key without the prefix.\n\n### Data configurations\n\n| Key | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `iconName` | `home` | Popular-icon dropdown selection |\n| `customIcon` | _(empty)_ | Any Material Symbols name. Overrides `iconName` when set. |\n\n### Data display\n\n| Key | Default | Description / Example |\n|---|---|---|\n| `iconSize` | `0` | Pixels; `0` = auto-scale. Example: `\"icon_library.icon_library.iconSize\": \"48\"` |\n| `hAlign` | `center` | `left` / `center` / `right` |\n| `vAlign` | `center` | `top` / `center` / `bottom` |\n| `rotation` | `0` | Degrees 0\u2013360 |\n| `showLabel` | `no` | `yes` shows label below icon |\n| `labelText` | _(empty)_ | Static label text (overridden by SPL `label` column) |\n| `labelSize` | `0` | Pixels; `0` = auto-scale |\n| `labelColor` | `#94A3B8` | Hex |\n\n### Tooltip / theme (new in 1.6.0)\n\n| Key | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `tooltip` | `off` | `off` / `auto` (when a search is attached) / `always`. On hover, shows the resolved label, icon name, and threshold value. |\n| `theme` | `auto` | `auto` / `dark` / `light`. Detects Splunk's body class and swaps factory-default colors for label / background / shadow so the viz reads correctly on light dashboards. Explicit user-set colors are preserved. |\n\n### Icon style\n\n| Key | Default | Description / Example |\n|---|---|---|\n| `iconColor` | `#06B6D4` | Hex color of the icon |\n| `bgShape` | `none` | `none` / `circle` / `rounded_rect` / `square` |\n| `bgColor` | `#1E293B` | Background fill hex |\n| `bgOpacity` | `1` | 0\u20131 |\n| `bgPadding` | `16` | Pixels between icon and bg edge |\n| `bgRadius` | `12` | Corner radius (rounded_rect only) |\n| `shadow` | `no` | Drop shadow toggle |\n| `shadowColor` / `Blur` / `OffsetX` / `OffsetY` | `#000000` / `8` / `0` / `4` | Shadow controls |\n| `glow` | `no` | Glow toggle |\n| `glowColor` | `#06B6D4` | Glow hex |\n| `glowSize` | `12` | Glow radius (px) |\n\n### Threshold colors (Section 6)\n\n| Key | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `thresholdField` | `value` | SPL column name driving the band |\n| `thresholdLow` / `High` | `50` / `90` | Two breakpoints |\n| `thresholdDirection` | `high_good` | `high_good` or `high_bad` |\n| `thresholdColorLow/Mid/High` | red / amber / green | Per-band colors |\n| `colorIcon` / `Label` / `Glow` / `Bg` | `yes` / `no` / `no` / `no` | Apply band color to that element |\n\n### Threshold effects (Section 7)\n\n| Key | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `thresholdIconLow/Mid/High` | _(empty)_ | Per-band icon-name override. Empty = no swap. |\n| `thresholdGlowScaleLow/Mid/High` | `1` | Multiplier on glow size when in that band. `0` disables glow. |\n| `thresholdPulse` | `no` | `no` / `critical` / `warning` / `critical_and_warning` |\n| `thresholdPulseSpeed` | `1` | Pulses per second |",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_sec5": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 5. Drilldown / Click Interactions\n\nDrilldown is **automatic** \u2014 there is no per-viz toggle. The viz fires a click event on every click; the dashboard decides what to do with it via Studio's `eventHandlers`.\n\n> **Note for 1.5.x \u2192 1.6.x migration:** earlier versions exposed `drilldownUrl` and `drilldownNewTab` formatter fields for direct URL navigation. Both were removed in 1.6.0 to eliminate the `javascript:` XSS surface. Build the target URL in a downstream token consumer or use Studio's native `drilldown.linkToUrl` handler instead.\n\n### Wiring it up\n\nThree things must line up:\n\n1. The panel must be backed by a **real `ds.search`** (e.g. `| makeresults | eval icon=\"security\"`). `ds.test` mock data does NOT propagate drilldown context to `setToken`.\n2. Panel `options` must include `\"drilldown\": \"all\"` \u2014 without it, Studio silently drops the click.\n3. `eventHandlers` array with `drilldown.setToken` using `\"key\": \"row.icon.value\"` (or `\"label\"` / `\"color\"`).\n\n```json\n\"viz_my_icon\": {\n  \"type\": \"icon_library.icon_library\",\n  \"dataSources\": { \"primary\": \"ds_event\" },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"backgroundColor\": \"transparent\",\n    \"drilldown\": \"all\"\n  },\n  \"eventHandlers\": [{\n    \"type\": \"drilldown.setToken\",\n    \"options\": {\n      \"tokens\": [{ \"token\": \"selected_icon\", \"key\": \"row.icon.value\" }]\n    }\n  }]\n}\n```\n\n### Click payload \u2014 what setToken can capture\n\nThe viz emits `{icon, label?, color?}`, which Splunk maps to a synthetic row. Reference each field via `row.<field>.value`:\n\n| `key` | Resolves to |\n|---|---|\n| `\"row.icon.value\"` | The resolved icon name |\n| `\"row.label.value\"` | The label text (only present if a label is rendered) |\n| `\"row.color.value\"` | The resolved icon color (hex) |\n\n> **Wrong pattern to avoid:** `\"key\": \"click.value\"` (native chart syntax) does not work for custom-viz `FIELD_VALUE_DRILLDOWN` payloads. Always use the `row.<field>.value` form here.\n\n### Capturing multiple values in one click\n\n```json\n\"eventHandlers\": [{\n  \"type\": \"drilldown.setToken\",\n  \"options\": {\n    \"tokens\": [\n      { \"token\": \"selected_icon\",  \"key\": \"row.icon.value\"  },\n      { \"token\": \"selected_label\", \"key\": \"row.label.value\" },\n      { \"token\": \"selected_color\", \"key\": \"row.color.value\" }\n    ]\n  }\n}]\n```\n\n### Live demo (right column)\n\nClick the icon. The panel below it shows the captured `$selected_icon$` token, set via `drilldown.setToken` with `key: \"row.icon.value\"`.",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_drilldown_demo": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_drilldown_icons"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconColor": "#06B6D4",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgShape": "circle",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgColor": "#0F172A",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgPadding": "16",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glow": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowColor": "#06B6D4",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glowSize": "12",
        "drilldown": "all"
      },
      "eventHandlers": [
        {
          "type": "drilldown.setToken",
          "options": {
            "tokens": [
              {
                "token": "selected_icon",
                "key": "row.icon.value"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "viz_drilldown_consumer": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "**Last clicked**\n\n`$selected_icon$`",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_sec6": {
      "type": "splunk.markdown",
      "options": {
        "markdown": "## 6. Threshold Colors\n\nThe **Threshold colors** formatter section drives icon, label, glow, and/or background color from a numeric SPL column. Two breakpoints define three bands.\n\n### How it works\n\nValue < `thresholdLow` \u2192 low band\nValue \u2208 `[thresholdLow, thresholdHigh)` \u2192 mid band\nValue \u2265 `thresholdHigh` \u2192 high band\n\nWith `thresholdDirection = high_good`: low band gets the *low color* (red by default), high band gets the *high color* (green). Flip to `high_bad` for metrics where high values are worse (errors, latency).\n\n### Minimal example \u2014 color the icon by `value`\n\n```spl\n| makeresults | eval value=97\n```\n\nFormatter defaults (`thresholdLow=50`, `thresholdHigh=90`, `direction=high_good`, `colorIcon=yes`) classify value 97 in the **high band** \u2192 green icon. No JSON changes needed.\n\n### Coloring multiple elements at once\n\n```json\n\"options\": {\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.colorIcon\":  \"yes\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.colorGlow\":  \"yes\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.colorBg\":    \"no\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.colorLabel\": \"no\"\n}\n```\n\n### Custom thresholds \u2014 high=bad latency metric\n\n```json\n\"options\": {\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdField\":     \"latency_ms\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdLow\":       \"200\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdHigh\":      \"500\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.thresholdDirection\": \"high_bad\"\n}\n```\n\n### Power user \u2014 DOS expression instead of formatter\n\nFor 5+ bands, gradient interpolation, or exact-match coloring, use Dashboard Studio's Dynamic Options Syntax on any color option. Set the matching `colorIcon/Label/Glow/Bg` toggle to `no` so the formatter engine doesn't override DOS.\n\n```json\n\"options\": {\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.iconColor\":\n    \"> primary | seriesByName('uptime_pct') | lastPoint() | rangeValue(colors)\",\n  \"icon_library.icon_library.colorIcon\": \"no\"\n},\n\"context\": {\n  \"colors\": [\n    { \"to\": 95,             \"value\": \"#EF4444\" },\n    { \"from\": 95, \"to\": 99, \"value\": \"#F59E0B\" },\n    { \"from\": 99,           \"value\": \"#22C55E\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Precedence (highest wins)\n\n1. Explicit SPL `color` column \u2014 always wins\n2. Formatter threshold band (when `colorIcon`/etc. is yes)\n3. DOS expression on `iconColor`/`labelColor`/`glowColor`/`bgColor`\n4. Static formatter color picker\n\n### Live demo (right column)\n\nThree tiles, same configuration, different `value` rows \u2014 `20`, `65`, `97`. `colorGlow=yes` so the glow takes the band color too.",
        "fontColor": "#E2E8F0",
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "fontSize": "default"
      }
    },
    "viz_thr_low": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_thr_low"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
        "icon_library.icon_library.iconName": "monitor_heart",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgShape": "circle",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgColor": "#0F172A",
        "icon_library.icon_library.bgPadding": "12",
        "icon_library.icon_library.glow": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.colorGlow": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.showLabel": "yes",
        "icon_library.icon_library.labelText": "20 \u2014 low",
        "icon_library.icon_library.labelColor": "#94A3B8"
      }
    },
    "viz_thr_mid": {
      "type": "icon_library.icon_library",
      "dataSources": {
        "primary": "ds_thr_mid"
      },
      "options": {
        "backgroundColor": "transparent",
